sql:
SELECT SUM(basket_spend) AS total_spent_by_loyalty_members
FROM sales_transactions
WHERE customer_id IN (
  SELECT customer_id
  FROM loyalty_members
);

external_knowledge:
- High total sales indicate strong store performance; 
- High average transaction value suggests that customers spend more per visit, which is typically desirable; 
- High customer satisfaction (average feedback rating) is crucial for repeat business and reputation; 
- Promotion effectiveness is a measure of how well promotional activities contribute to overall sales, with higher values indicating better performance.

/top 10 biggest spenders refers to the 10 customers with the highest total spending; 
Customers are ranked based on their total spending in descending order; 
The top 10 customers are determined by the rank, where the customer with the highest spending has rank 1.
